items.toString: K&K [#60] Merge Profiles + Delete Incomplete Packets

items.fromString:
A request has come through from Tiffany to merge two profiles. She has been doing double hiring (hiring with two packets) and for one worker the 2nd time around it got put into a second profile. 

*JOSE SANCHEZ REYNOZO* - 3221 

*JOSE SANCHEZ REYNOZO* - DUPE3221



Can we Delete the Incomplete Packet in 3221 (started June 24th, 2023, 5:52 AM) That way when the new packet comes in from DUPE3221 there will be only 1 from CE Farm and 1 K&K: New Hire packet. Both are currently in Awaiting Signature (as of right now [11:22am pst])

They also provided me with a list of “incomplete packets” that they do not need. We can delete the profiles and the packets associated with them: [Preview attachment Screenshot 2023-06-27 113404.png|https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0?ui=2&ik=80f7c834d5&attid=0.1&permmsgid=msg-f:1769882557037966044&th=188fe2cef26872dc&view=att&disp=safe]

!Screenshot 2023-06-27 113404.png|width=91.66666666666666%!



Please let me know if you have any questions regarding this request!

For the first person. 

{quote}JOSE SANCHEZ REYNOZO - 3221 
JOSE SANCHEZ REYNOZO - DUPE3221 {quote}

Please see the discussion in slack [~accountid:63113ce88473817d7d04b3d3] [https://ganazhq.slack.com/archives/C02MW62K7U0/p1687994636058179|https://ganazhq.slack.com/archives/C02MW62K7U0/p1687994636058179|smart-link]

{noformat}id,first_name,last_name,employee_id
776996,JESUS GREGORIO,PEREZ HERNANDEZ,10087
776998,JESUS GREGORIO,PEREZ HERNANDEZ,3560
777000,JESUS GREGORIO,PEREZ HERNANDEZ,35601
778406,MAY,Ganaz,Test 300239
624713,MARIANO,CASTILLO GORDIAN,004002
571279,FERNANDO,CORONA CASTRO,3128{noformat}

Deleted.

[~accountid:63113ce88473817d7d04b3d3]  For the remaining person in the screenshot. 
Melissa Boydston, eeid: {{01010}}, personid: {{603232}} I see that she has a signed card packet from 2022-11-08. 
Her paycard is with an empty balance.  Was this a test by an office person? Do we still want to delete this profile? 


_My own notes to myself : to delete a cardholder we need to follow these steps:_ [https://ganaz.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SOFTWARE/pages/312869091/Deleting+Person+Entries|https://ganaz.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SOFTWARE/pages/312869091/Deleting+Person+Entries|smart-link]

Ah I see! Then I think it would be best to keep the profile but just delete the incomplete packet instance. I do know this was a test as Melissa is one of the HR Staff over there but if she was testing paycards I think it is best to leave that profile intact but just remove the incomplete packet. Thoughts?
that works.
Melissa’s empty packet deleted

This is also completed: JOSE SANCHEZ REYNOZO - 3221 
JOSE SANCHEZ REYNOZO - DUPE3221. 

Jose Reynozo now has two signed i9s asked for. 
Melissa has one profile left, with signed paycard agreement
Perfect! Thank you so much, [~accountid:613e6eaa1238e8007108f513]!!!

comments.body:
[~accountid:63113ce88473817d7d04b3d3] I did what the ticket says but I don’t think this is actually right.

Now the two real profiles each have a duplicate completed of the same packet. I don’t actually think this should have been a *merge*, just *delete* (which seems to be the case the vast majority of the time).

I’m guessing you will want me to delete the duplicate completed packets:

[https://app.ganaz.com/o/0/company/1311/hiring/759048|https://app.ganaz.com/o/0/company/1311/hiring/759048]
[https://app.ganaz.com/o/0/company/1311/hiring/731860|https://app.ganaz.com/o/0/company/1311/hiring/731860]

Hi Daniel, 

No worries! Thank you so much for checking. I did purposefully request that the old hiring info be in there as they do seem many days prior (8 and 6 days prospectively) but I can ask the customer! I will let you know what they say!
Ok, we will keep it open and see if we need to remove any of the documents. Otherwise I’ll close it in a day or two and we can open a new ticket if it becomes an issue again.
[~accountid:62780ad493111000689ece08]  + [~accountid:63113ce88473817d7d04b3d3]  can this be closed?
Yep! This one is all good—thank you, team!
